方案是从国际货币基金组织借<a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-02-08/pakistan-needs-new-imf-funds-to-repay-old-imf-debt-baqir-says?sref=R8NfLgwS">更多的钱来</a>偿还已经欠下的债务。正如你所预料的那样，这一战略导致巴基斯坦的外债多年来<a href="https://blogs.lse.ac.uk/southasia/2019/04/10/pakistan-foreign-reserves-and-the-debt-crisis/">不断增加</a>。</p><p>不过，最近巴基斯坦也开始从其他国家借入大量资金——沙特阿拉伯和阿联酋， <a href="https://asia.nikkei.com/Spotlight/Belt-and-Road/Squeezed-by-debt-and-the-US-Pakistan-slows-Belt-and-Road-projects">尤其是中国</a>。中国的大部分债务与“一带一路”项目有关，该项目本应在巴基斯坦建设新的高质量基础设施，但……<a href="https://www.geopolitica.info/china-pakistan-economic-corridor/">没有</a>。</p><p>现在，巴基斯坦和<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/how-chinas-debt-traps-actually-work">许多“一带一路”借款国</a>一样，发现所有这些中国贷款并不取决于这些项目是否真正成功。中国褐皮书董事总经理 Shehad Qazi<a href="https://twitter.com/shehzadhqazi/status/1758011711678726493">解释道</a>： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F72f497fa-80a7-41ef-b849-4cc0d56452d5_926x768.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F72f497fa-80a7-41ef-b849-4cc0d56452d5_926x768.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F72f497fa-80a7-41ef-b849-4cc0d56452d5_926x768.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F72f497fa-80a7-41ef-b849-4cc0d56452d5_926x768.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive