%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3f0f4c96-d645-4e57-bbe7-5d4be98e6007_796x575.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源：<a href="https://www.sustainabilitybynumbers.com/p/renewables-waste">汉娜·里奇（Hannah Ritchie）</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>无论如何，我认为您从所有这一切中的收获都应该是，绿色能源对于真实而不是由环保主义者和政府大规模驱动的时尚。现在存在这些工具来解决气候危机；我们要做的就是捡起它们并使用它们。</p><h4>减少排放并不意味着降解</h4><p>最后，值得一提的是解决气候变化对其他经济的影响。一些气候活动家认为放弃化石燃料需要<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/degrowth-we-cant-let-it-happen-here">降解</a>。基本思想是，排放和GDP是不可撤销的 - 从长远来看，没有办法增加GDP，同时也放弃了石油，煤炭和天然气。</p><p>幸运的是，这完全是错误的。一份新的<a href="https://www.iea.org/commentaries/the-relationship-between-growth-in-gdp-and-co2-has-loosened-it-needs-to-be-cut-completely">IEA报告</a>显示，全球GDP越来越与二氧化碳排放量息息相关： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F41359a05-df8c-4584-9148-1f61a752ebed_636x722.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F41359a05-df8c-4584-9148-1f61a752ebed_636x722.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F41359